52.title: Abrazo de Oso
52.plot: Romeo gives a surprise gift to Simona for the good gesture she had with Lula.

53.title: Tan Cerca, Tan Lejos
53.plot: After the "rejection" of Simona, Romeo returns to bet on his relationship with Lula. The relationship between Junior and Chipi is consolidated.

54.title: Hay Química Entre los Dos
54.plot: Dante takes advantage of Romeo's departure to get closer to Simona.

55.title: Juntos, Aún en La Adversidad
55.plot: Romeo and Simona are locked in a cemetery.

56.title: El Beso de La Discordia
56.plot: Simona discovers Lula kissing another boy and tells Dante everything. Junior will have a talk with Blas.

57.title: Sintonía de Amor
57.plot: Simona calls Romeo's program on the radio to confess that she is in love.

58.title: Una Revelación Inesperada
58.plot: Dante listens to a conversation between Romeo and Mauro. Simona will try to comfort him. Diego decides to organize a dinner for Junior to make the "official presentation" of his girlfriend.

59.title: Amor Fugitivo
59.plot: Simona and Dante escape from the mansion and spend the night together.

60.title: Un Momento Difícil
60.plot: Simona faints after a fight with her sister and Romeo helps her.

61.title: La Hora de la Verdad
61.plot: Simona looks for Marilina's daughter and begins to suspect something. Trini and Ailín will invite Simona to a particular bar.

62.title: Del Amor al Drama
62.plot: Simona goes out to have fun with her friends, but receives terrible news. Marilina has reached a turning point: she feels it is time to reveal the truth to her daughter.

63.title: Una Señal del Destino
63.plot: After the accident, Rosa is unconscious and will have a special connection with Simona. The young woman will receive news that will leave her very close to fulfilling a dream.

64.title: Voces en Rivalidad
64.plot: Simona and Romeo face each other in a musical contest.

65.title: El Amor Está en El Aire
65.plot: Romeo recognizes, without realizing that he is on the radio, that he is in love with Simona.

66.title: El Poder del Verdadero Amor
66.plot: The eldest of the Guerrico nephews decides to put an end to his relationship with Lula to start a romance with Simona.

67.title: Adiós Para Siempre
67.plot: Lula tells Romeo that she is pregnant and they kiss before Simona's eyes.

68.title: Amor Sin Retorno
68.plot: Simona finds out about Lula's pregnancy and understands that, given the circumstances, she must renounce her love for Romeo.

69.title: Amarga espera
69.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

70.title: Sueño Compartido
70.plot: Simona stayed to sleep after Ailín's farewell and shared the bed with Dante, but his older brother surprised them in bed.

71.title: Escuchar a La Razón o Al Corazón
71.plot: Simona accompanies Rosa to a medical check-up and Lula is taking her first ultrasound, accompanied by Romeo. Upon noticing her presence, the eldest of the Guerrico nephews will feel at a crossroads: he deeply loves Simona but understands that he must stay with Lula at this special moment.

72.title: Enfermera por Un Día
72.plot: Simona shows herself closer and closer to Dante. Junior is confused. He can not figure out what happens to him when he sees Blas. His presence alters him and makes him uncomfortable.

73.title: Tercero en Discordia
73.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

74.title: Mal de Amores
74.plot: Dante silently suffers for the closeness of Simona with the music producer. In fact, he will have a "love crisis". Seeing him so anguished, Simona will go to "his rescue". Junior will try to tell his brothers about his feelings for Blas. But fear will stop him. Taking advantage that Dante stays to sleep at Simona's the youngest of the Guerrico will invite Blas to spend the night there.

75.title: Identidad Desconocida
75.plot: Dante receives a news about the identity of his father. He seek consolation once again in Simona. On the other hand, Simona will find Junior having breakfast with Blas and will start to think about what happens between them. In fact, she ask Junior about the situation, but he does not know how to respond.

76.title: Un Encuentro Secreto
76.plot: A romantic getaway will complicate things. Diego and Marilina secretly meet, but Siena finds out. Junior will finally be encouraged to tell Simona about his secret encounter with Blas.

77.title: Episode #1.77
77.plot: Simona kisses Bautista and Romeo is an involuntary witness of the scene.

78.title: Verdad y Consecuencia
78.plot: Junior will be encouraged to tell Blas what he really feels. Romeo tells Simona that he is jealous of Bautista, but he wants to continue with Lula.

79.title: Amor en Suspenso
79.plot: Junior, increasingly anguished, will again confess to Blas that he can not stop thinking about him. Simona decides to move away from Romeo in the face of Lula's pressures.

80.title: Simular por Amor
80.plot: Simona kisses Bautista so that Lula does not suspect that she is still in love with Romeo. Blas resigns from Dante's bar. He is confused with Junior.

imdb.plot outline: Simona is a happy and fun young woman, sure of herself and of what she wants, who had to overcome difficulties since she was very young: she had to learn to grow up without her parents as guides. Marilina, Simona's mother, is involved in a confused and violent episode for which she ends up imprisoned, far from her beloved daughter, who is referred to an orphanage, in the care of Rosa, with whom she grows up happy and loved by her adoptive mom, and will not hesitate to replace her as a domestic employee in the house of Guerrico. In the big family house, she must place herself under Diego's orders. In addition, under that same roof she will be reunited with Romeo, the eldest of the three nephews of her boss, whom she knows since childhood. That closeness will go, little by little, awakening the love between both of them. Meanwhile, Marilina leaves prison and gets a job at the Guerrico trauma clinic. There she will meet Diego, of whom she will fall madly in love, even more when she finds out that he has become a great reference for her daughter. Simona has a very clear goal: to succeed as a singer, her true passion in life. Music will always be her best company. Until life surprises her with the appearance of that other great and wonderful support that is her mother.

Marilina, _Simona_ (qv)'s mother, is involved in a confused and violent episode for which she ends up imprisoned, far from her beloved daughter, who is referred to an orphanage, in the care of Rosa, with whom she grows up happy and loved by her adoptive mom, and will not hesitate to replace her as a domestic employee in the house of Guerrico. In the big family house, she must place herself under Diego's orders. In addition, under that same roof she will be reunited with Romeo, the eldest of the three nephews of her boss, whom she knows since childhood. That closeness will go, little by little, awakening the love between both of them. Meanwhile, Marilina leaves prison and gets a job at the Guerrico trauma clinic. There she will meet Diego, of whom she will fall madly in love, even more when she finds out that he has become a great reference for her daughter. _Simona_ (qv) has a very clear goal: to succeed as a singer, her true passion in life. Music will always be her best company. Until life surprises her with the appearance of that other great and wonderful support that is her mother.
